8 SECTION 2. A new section to chapter 25-13 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
9 and enacted as follows:
10 Health care provider documentation - Requirements - Prohibited acts - Penalty .
11 1. A health care provider may not produce documentation relating to an individual's need
12 for an assistance animal unless the health care provider:
13 a. Is actively licensed to practice medicine in the state;
14 b. Is qualified and licensed to evaluate and diagnose disabilities and has performed
15 a disability assessment on the individual for which documentation is produced;
16 c. Has engaged with the individual in - person or remotely in at least two sessions
17 before issuing documentation determining the individual requires an assistance
18 animal; and
19 d. Performs a clinical evaluation of the individual no less than thirty days before
20 producing documentation regarding the individual's need for an assistance
21 animal.
22 2. Documentation issued by a health care provider regarding an individual's need for an
23 assistance animal must include:
24 a. The effective and expiration dates of the documentation;
25 b. The signature of the healthcare provider;
26 c. The license number of the health care provider;
27 d. The type of professional license held by the health care provider; and
28 e. Evidence establishing a therapeutic relationship with the individual no less than
29 thirty days before producing the documentation regarding the individual's need
30 for an assistance animal.
