1 3. A health care provider may not represent or attempt to represent that an individual has
2 a disability requiring an assistance animal when an individual is not disabled or does
3 not need an assistance animal on account of the individual's disability.
4 4. An individual may not represent or attempt to represent to a third party that the
5 individual has a disability requiring an assistance animal when the individual is not
6 disabled or does not require an assistance animal on account of the individual's
7 disability.
8 5. An individual receiving documentation from a health care provider regarding the
9 individual's need for an assistance animal under this section shall renew the
10 documentation within one year of issuance. A documentation not renewed within one
11 year of issuance is deemed expired and ineffective.
12 6. Any person in violation of this section is guilty of an infraction for a first offense and a
13 class B misdemeanor for a second or subsequent offense .
14 7. This section may not be construed to restrict or modify any federal or state laws
15 relating to an individual's rights for reasonable accommodation and equal access to
16 housing, including rights afforded in accordance with the Fair Housing Act [Pub . L .
17 90 - 284; 82 Stat. 81; 42 U.S.C. 3601, et seq.] and the Americans with Disabilities Ac t
18 [Pub . L. 101 - 336; 104 Stat. 327; 42 U.S.C 12101 et seq.] .
19 SECTION 3. A new section to chapter 25-13 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
20 and enacted as follows:
21 Sale of assistance animals - Notice requirements - Penalty .
22 1. A person selling, providing an animal for use as an assistance animal, or providing a
23 certificate or letter certifying an animal for use as an assistance animal shall provide a
24 written notice to the buyer or recipient of the animal stating the assistance animal:
25 a. Does not have the special training required to qualify as a service animal; and
26 b. Is not entitled to the rights and privileges accorded by law to a service animal.
27 2. The written notice under subsection 1 must be printed in bold in at least twelve - poin t
28 typeface.
29 3. A person violating this section is guilty of an infraction for a first offense and a class B
30 misdemeanor for a second or subsequent offense.
