6 SECTION 4. AMENDMENT. Section 47-16-07.5 of the North Dakota Century Code is
7 amended and reenacted as follows:
8 47-16-07.5. Disability documentation for service or assistance animal in rental
9 dwelling.
10 1. A landlord may require reliable supporting documentation be provided by a tenant of a
11 rental dwelling that is subject to a no pets policy, if the tenant asserts a disability
12 requiring a service animal or assistance animal be allowed as an accommodation on
13 the rented premises under any provision of law.
14 2. Reliable supporting documentation may be provided by a physician or medical
15 professional who does not operate in this state solely to provide certification for
16 service or assistance animals. Reliable supporting documentation must confirm the
17 tenant's disability and the relationship between the tenant's disability and the need for
18 the requested accommodation. A landlord may not require supporting documentation
19 from a tenant if the tenant's disability or disability-related need for a service animal or
20 assistance animal is readily apparent or already known to the landlord.
21 3. Documentation provided by a tenant of a rental dwelling that is subject to a no pets
22 policy which asserts a disability that requires an assistance animal must comply with
23 the documentation requirements under section 2 of this Act .
